==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Junta
<hw>Jun"ta</hw> <pr>(j⟦ucr⟧n"t⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Juntas</plw> <pr>(j⟦ucr⟧n"t⟦adot⟧z)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[Sp., fr. L. <ets>junctus</ets> joined, <ets>p. p.</ets> of
<ets>jungere</ets> to join. See <er>Join</er>, and cf.
<er>Junto</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A council; a convention; a
tribunal; an assembly; esp., the grand council of state in
Spain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A junto.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A small committee or group self-appointed to serve
as the government of a country, usually just after a coup d'etat or
revolution, and often composed primarily of military men. The term is
used mostly in Latin American countries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Junto</ent>⟦br⟧
